metadata.name: compendia
metadata.description:
Human forms, as well as other forms, are temporal compendia of intemporal elements.

Elemental things exist eternally, but constituted or compounded things, that is, forms, lose in wholeness elemental eternity.

How tenuous are constituted things! If it is form, it shall die; if it is thin, fluxing, formless, it is eternal.

â€”From an unpublished essay by A.R. Ammons written in 1950

Trained with Generative Adversarial Networks on of a collection of underwater organisms, reconstructions of underlying patterns and spatial representations of sub-aquatic microclimates.
